<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-17T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="710" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./1–1745: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-17T18:00:00+07:00">January
                                    17, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 17—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>80. Consul [at] Tihwa reports following based on interviews January 12
                            with General Chu: Insurgents now number about 15,000; they show evidence
                            of military training and are generously supplied with mortars, machine
                            guns and ammunition. Situation of Chinese garrisoning in airfield
                            desperate. Huiyuan fell to insurgents on December 25 and Suiting
                            December 30. Chinese troops retiring to point on Horgos–Tihwa highway
                            between Chingho and Hsin Erhtai.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>